    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nWith `notermguicolors` the default colorscheme pulls all its colors from the 17-255. This is a bold change from the old default colorscheme which only uses the [0-15 ansi colors](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code#Colors). The benefit this had was that it used whatever color palette was defined in the terminal, and thus whatever the user configures themselves. Now the new default colorscheme is quite jaring and completely deviates from the colors used in the terminal.\r\n\r\nNote I think it's good to distinguish the two components of a colorscheme which often get conflated:\r\n1. The palette. The actual values for each color, e.g. What is red, blue, etc.\r\n2. How the palette is used.\r\n\r\nThis issue only wishes to change how palette is determined with `notermguicolors`, not how it is used.\r\n\r\nAlso note, I believe the old default colorscheme only had issues with 2 which #26334 addresses very well.\r\n\r\n## Proposal\r\n\r\nThe current color palette almost falls into the 16 color space, however it contains 20 colors as it uses 8 colors for gray.\r\n\r\n```\r\nDark:\r\nblue    = \"#005078\"\r\ncyan    = \"#007676\"\r\ngreen   = \"#015825\"\r\ngrey1   = \"#0a0b10\"\r\ngrey2   = \"#1c1d23\"\r\ngrey3   = \"#2c2e33\"\r\ngrey4   = \"#4f5258\"\r\nmagenta = \"#4c0049\"\r\nred     = \"#5e0009\"\r\nyellow  = \"#6e5600\"\r\n\r\nLight:\r\nblue    = \"#9fd8ff\"\r\ncyan    = \"#83efef\"\r\ngreen   = \"#aaedb7\"\r\ngrey1   = \"#ebeef5\"\r\ngrey2   = \"#d7dae1\"\r\ngrey3   = \"#c4c6cd\"\r\ngrey4   = \"#9b9ea4\"\r\nmagenta = \"#ffc3fa\"\r\nred     = \"#ffbcb5\"\r\nyellow  = \"#f4d88c\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nTherefore we should be able to rework the colorscheme to only use the `cterm0-15` colors and provide a terminal configuration for users who wish use the new Nvim palette. Since the palette requires 4 additional colors either:\r\n- pull these from the 17-255 space.\r\n- merge these shades of grey into white, black, \"dark white\" and \"bright black\".\r\n\r\n\r\n## Other points:\r\n- The current `notermguicolors` differs quite a bit to the `termguicolors` version. If instead we use\r\nthe 0-15 space and provide a terminal configuration, then it is possible for the `notermguicolors` version\r\nto much more closely match the `termguicolors` version. If the user wishes.\r\n  - This will be useful for anyone who SSH's into machines that have Neovim but not their default config and/or without the correct terminfo to enable truecolor.\r\n- The 256 color set is not usually configurable in terminals.\r\n   - Wezterm **does allow** defining the full 256 range via OSC escape sequences: https://wezfurlong.org/wezterm/escape-sequences.html#operating-system-command-sequences\r\n- Defining a background will change/disrupt any setups who use transparent terminals.",
