            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Even though I use a terminal with truecolor support, I still often find I'm in situtations where the shell isn't properly set up. \r\n\r\nIf we could detect these situations, adding a 16c fallback would be a no-brainer.\r\n\r\n> From my perspective, the whole 256 color thing never properly took off and is now superseded by truecolor.\r\n\r\nThat is a fair argument. \r\n\r\nPersonally, I agree and consider `notgc` purely under the usability and accessibility point of view -- which I'm afraid will be even harder to manage under this even stricter constraint. Which leads me to: Unless you suggest reverting `notgc` to the old default, you should propose such a colorscheme as the person who cares most about it.\r\n",
