            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Keep in mind 256 colors is the default experience for new users and `nvim --clean`.\r\n\r\nSo if we can find a path here without introducing lots of random colors, no objection. For example, \"magenta\" could be used for `Special` or something infrequent. But compromises in the 'notermguicolors' variant should not bleed into the 'termguicolors' variant.\r\n\r\n> Since the palette requires 4 additional colors either:\r\n>\r\n> * pull these from the 17-255 space.\r\n> * merge these shades of grey into white, black, \"dark white\" and \"bright black\".\r\n\r\nEither SGTM.",
