            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Sensing a no-win situation. The way we deal with this kind of \"terminal-tradition hell\" is to declare bankruptcy and focus on the common case.\r\n\r\n- If there are some small low-risk tweaks we can make to improve the 16-color situation, fine. \r\n- But we don't need to fully support 16-color, as long as it \"readable\". \r\n- People who care about full 16-color fidelity can use `:colors vim`.\r\n\r\n> This will be useful for anyone who SSH's into machines that have Neovim but not their default config and/or without the correct terminfo to enable truecolor.\r\n\r\n'termguicolors' forces RGB, terminfo is ignored: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/66f1563c7a48d76f99c89e32de030e57af2abfb4/src/nvim/tui/tui.c#L673",
