        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">The most problematic is indeed 4 additional grey colors. They define how UI looks. Pulling these from 16-255 space will not lead to entirely usable palette, as those can equal to some of user's 0-15.\r\n\r\nThis seems like a very unlikely scenario. We are only discussing using different shades of gray from 16-255, and 0-15 has only two “grays” (7 and 8, though arguably only 8), at worst we would conflict with two shades defined by the user, and even then that is only if the user *happens* to use the same colors that we pick (unlikely).\r\n\r\nThis seems like the best approach to me. I’m strongly in favor of going this route, unless there is some aspect here I am missing or overlooking. ",
            "created_at": "2023-12-04T13:39:50Z",
