        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Also the crux of the issue is that I want the scheme to use my configured colors, not some hardcoded set I can't change without having nvim configured.\r\n\r\nAnd I would consider \"has default color scheme\" to mean both custom palette and how highlight groups use them. I don't think it is reasonable to expect any color scheme (even default) to be only \"how palette colors are assigned to highlight groups\". This is where an actual decision of what is best needed.\r\n\r\nIn the end, the end goal is to \"be good with `nvim --clean`\". I personally can not see a way of being good using only 0-15.",
